title: Your guide to live music happening around the Bay
text:
Your guide to live music happening around the Bay Hannah Baker | 21st Oct 2015 12:53 PM Updated: 12:53 PM Hannah Baker The Screaming Jets will perform at the Beach House Hotel on Thursday night. Mike Richards GLA110915NITE 
When: Thursday from 7.30pm. 
Where: The Beach House Hotel functions room, 344 The Esplanade, Scarness. 
What: Rock away with the Screaming Jets who are touring Australia. The Newcastle band is celebrating its 25th year together and is sure to get the audience riled. 
Cost: $40. Buy from the Beach House gaming room or visit http://www.ticketmaster.com.au 

When: Friday from 8pm. 
Where: Hoolihans Irish Restaurant and Bar, 382 Esplanade, Torquay. 
What: Voice of Urban 2014 winner and acoustic sensation Wal Neilsen to sing tracks penned by himself from his album Night Rider, along with other tunes. 
Cost: Free. Watch Voice of Urban 2014 winner Wal Neilsen at Hoolihans Irish Restaurant and Bar. Robin-lee Reidy 
When: Friday from 7.30pm. 
Where: Anzac Lounge, 11 Torquay Road, Pialba. 
What: Enjoy tracks from the 80's onwards to bop around to, in the comfort of the Hervey Bay RSL. 
Cost: Free.
